Package etomica.data

Class DataInfo

  • java.lang.Object
    • etomica.data.DataInfo
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IDataInfo, java.io.Serializable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    DataDouble.DataInfoDouble, DataDoubleArray.DataInfoDoubleArray, DataDoubleBDArray.DataInfoDoubleBDArray, DataGroup.DataInfoGroup, DataTensor.DataInfoTensor, DataVector.DataInfoVector

    public abstract class DataInfo
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable, IDataInfo
    Object associated with a Data instance and which provides descriptive information about the data encapsulated in it. Information is typically used when displaying or writing the data to file, or making new Data instances that can work with the one holding this DataInfo.

    A DataInfo instance is completely immutable.

    See Also:
    IData, Serialized Form
